<br>
I thought this was funny, but I am not sure if it is seen as the same by the general public on FV. Being new on the server, I thought I would tell you and see what you say.<br>
<br>
It began when my fairly low ranked Kati Sha and her friend were recovering from an onslaught of Loda Kai just inside the city of Shar Val. Up came a young one, who had not even attained his warder yet and seemed quite weak compared to us. His words as he approached us were something akin to &quot;U wanna hunt lol?&quot;. We did have problems understanding him as he seemed to suffer from a strange speech impediment making his tongue lol, but did try to converse.<br>
<br>
My friend tried to explain that we were much more versed in hunting them him, and that he would not learn from coming with us and that the places we went he would die quickly, but he semed to ignore what we said, stuck around and said many things peppered with &quot;u&quot;, &quot;lol&quot; and other strange words,  from what we could make out he still wanted to hunt with us.<br>
<br>
I then remembered what my grandmother had told me, a wise old tigress indeed. She had read in old scrolls about some beings called Doods, spirits from realms beyond that inhabit bodies on our world every now and then, recognizable by their strange speech. She had also told me some of their words, so I set out to try if this was one of those spirits.<br>
<br>
Trying this for the first time,  I said &quot;U want phat l3wtz nd gr8 xp?&quot;, an enchantment my grandmother told me would gain the trust of those spirits. But this scared the young one off, without further words he ran away. Even when he came back, he did not talk anymore at all. So mayhaps this enchantment in fact does drive the strange spirit of Dood from a young ones body, I just thought I would tell you so you can try this if you are willing to experiment. No guarantees however.<br>
<br>
